sql:
SELECT AVG(correlation_value) AS average_correlation
FROM data_correlations
WHERE factor_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "Annual temperature average" is the mean of the average monthly temperatures over a year;
- "CO2 correlation" refers to the statistical relationship between temperature and carbon dioxide levels;
- "Data collection method" indicates the technique used to gather temperature data, such as satellite or ground station.

- A temperature spike is an anomaly where the temperature suddenly rises above the normal range;
- The historical average is calculated based on data from all years before 1950;
- The resolution status 'pending' indicates that the anomaly has not yet been addressed.

- "stands tall as the sentinel" refers to the region with the highest average correlation with CO2 levels;
- "the breath of CO2" refers to CO2 levels;
- "the warmth of its seasons" refers to the average temperature data across the months.

sql:
SELECT T.region_id, AVG(T.jan) AS average_january_temperature
FROM temperature_data T
GROUP BY T.region_id;

external_knowledge:
