- The average temperature is a measure of the central tendency of the temperature data, representing the typical temperature for each month across the regions;
- The number of regions indicates how many areas are contributing to the temperature data, providing context on the sample size for each month.

- "temperature spike" refers to an abnormally high temperature reading;
- "pending" indicates that the anomaly has not been resolved yet;
- "average annual temperature" is calculated by averaging the monthly temperatures over a year.

- 'Ground Station' refers to a method of data collection that involves using ground-based instruments or stations;
